"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20-47-Isla-Vista-Stalking-Arrest-Suspect-Vehicle.jpeg?resize=532%2C407&ssl=1","description":"Santa Barbara County Sheriff’s Office detectives arrested Zachary Coughlin, the driver of the “mirror van,” for stalking on Monday night in Isla Vista around 10 p.m.","content":"<div class=\"single-post-content\">\n            <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Santa Barbara County Sheriff’s Office detectives arrested Zachary Coughlin, the driver of the “mirror van,” for stalking on Monday night in Isla Vista around 10 p.m., according to a press release from Raquel Zick, Sheriff’s Office spokesperson. </span></p>\n<div id=\"attachment_94479\" style=\"width: 542px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-94479\" data-attachment-id=\"94479\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2020-05-19/isla-vista-mirror-bus-driver-arrested-for-stalking/20-47-isla-vista-stalking-arrest-suspect-vehicle/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20-47-Isla-Vista-Stalking-Arrest-Suspect-Vehicle.jpeg?fit=532%2C407&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"532,407\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"Mirror van\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20-47-Isla-Vista-Stalking-Arrest-Suspect-Vehicle.jpeg?fit=250%2C191&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20-47-Isla-Vista-Stalking-Arrest-Suspect-Vehicle.jpeg?fit=532%2C407&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"wp-image-94479 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20-47-Isla-Vista-Stalking-Arrest-Suspect-Vehicle.jpeg?resize=532%2C407\" alt=\"\" width=\"532\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20-47-Isla-Vista-Stalking-Arrest-Suspect-Vehicle.jpeg?w=532&amp;ssl=1 532w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20-47-Isla-Vista-Stalking-Arrest-Suspect-Vehicle.jpeg?resize=250%2C191&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20-47-Isla-Vista-Stalking-Arrest-Suspect-Vehicle.jpeg?resize=430%2C330&amp;ssl=1 430w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 532px) 100vw, 532px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-94479\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Coughlin’s “mirror bus” was subsequently towed following his arrest. <em>Courtesy of Raquel Zick</em></p></div>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coughlin, 43, had been living in a converted bus, nicknamed the “mirror bus,” when Santa Barbara County Sheriff’s Office (SBSO) arrested Coughlin for “stalking a woman in the Isla Vista area,” Zick said. The bus was subsequently towed following his arrest. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He is currently in custody at the Santa Barbara County Jail and is being held on $200,000 bail, according to SBSO. According to Santa Barbara County Jail custody logs, Coughlin works for Grubhub, an online food delivery service. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">SBSO detectives conducted interviews with witnesses and administered “a behavioral threat assessment” of Coughlin, after SBSO “received various reports regarding Coughlin,” according to Zick. The detectives also searched through his social media accounts. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">“</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">[Coughlin] caught the attention of locals with his references on social media to the tragic mass murder that occurred in Isla Vista in 2014. His comments on social media also indicate that he shared ideology with “involuntary celibate” (incel) community,” Zick said. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the weeks prior to his arrest, community members took to the </span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/search/top/?q=mirror%20bus&amp;&amp;epa=SEARCH_BOX\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Facebook UCSB Free &amp; For Sale</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> group and </span><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/UCSantaBarbara/comments/glm3da/mirror_bus_in_isla_vista/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reddit threads</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to express their concerns about Coughlin’s behavior and to warn others to be aware of his presence in I.V., where he was frequently spotted parking along different streets in the area.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Isla Vista Community Services District (I.V. CSD) released a statement Tuesday afternoon following the arrest, stating that the board received messages from “many residents with safety concerns surrounding the ‘mirror van’” as well as about Coughling’s instagram account.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The I.V. CSD “immediately forwarded concerns posted on social media to law enforcement,” the statement said. Ethan Bertrand, one the CSD’s board members, said Isla Vistans “did the right thing” by posting online community warnings and responding to a “dangerous situation.”</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">“This type of community collaboration is necessary for keeping Isla Vista safe,” Bertrand said in the statement.  </span></p><div class=\"h5ab-print-button-container\"><div class=\"h5ab-print-button h5ab-print-button-left\" style=\"cursor: pointer; color: #555\"><i class=\"fa fa-print fa-lg\"></i>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span>Print</span></div></div>\n<div class=\"saboxplugin-wrap\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\" itemscope itemprop=\"author\"><div class=\"saboxplugin-gravatar\"><a href=\"https://dailynexus.com/author/sofia-mejias123/\"><img src=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_2108.jpg?w=888&amp;ssl=1\" alt